A spec-compliant boot program shall supply _#address-cells_ and _#size-cells_ on all nodes that have children.

If missing, a client program should assume a default value of 2 for _#address-cells_, and a value of 1 for _#size-cells_.

**Example:**

See the following devicetree excerpt:

```dts
soc {
    #address-cells = <1>;
    #size-cells = <1>;

    serial@4600 {
        compatible = "ns16550";
        reg = <0x4600 0x100>;
        clock-frequency = <0>;
        interrupts = <0xA 0x8>;
        interrupt-parent = <&ipic>;
    };
